@ijuma @ewencp 

Sorry for the delay. I was out of town.

@ijuma, your approach makes sense. But, we may have to write new condition for each data-type. As, we already accept `string`, to accept small `Long` / `Int` if the type is `Short`, 

```
String trimmed = null;
if (value instanceof String || value instanceof Number)
  trimmed = value.toString().trim();

case SHORT:
                    if (value instanceof Short) {
                        return (Short) value;
                    } else if (trimmed != null) {
                        return Short.parseShort(trimmed);
                    } else {
                        throw new ConfigException(name, value, "Expected value to be a short (16-bit integer), but it was a " + value.getClass().getName());
                    }
```

If user provides any abnormal value, they will get `NumberFormatException` / `ConfigException`. Is this approach ok ?
